  "text": "2 The final number of evaluations per picture ranges from 3 to 24. This number lies close to the number of evaluations employed in [CITATION_1] -who delete observations with fewer than three evaluations, and have on average nine evaluations per picture -and Hamermesh (2004) -who relies on four evaluations per picture. Clearly, one might worry that three evaluations is insufficient. To check this, we assess whether the coefficient of variation is higher for pictures with fewer evaluations (which would reflect more 'noise' surrounding the estimated evaluation). Comparing pictures obtaining less than 10 evaluations with those obtaining between 10 and 19 evaluations, we find no such effect. Hence, even relatively few evaluations appear to give a fairly precise estimate.",
